tactic for leveraging discovered credentials to assume the identity of the user

login basics:
    logon sessions: created after a user authenticated to a system, used to create an associated access token
                    holds info such as logon id, logon time, logon server, username, SID, and UPN
    access token: this token is what windows checks for access-based decisions, what whoami pulls info from
                  holds info such as token id, token type, ID of logon session, SIDs, integrity, privs, etc.
    credential cache: LSASS stores creds in memory for users with active logon sessions
            windows uses the access token to look up associated logon session and associated credential cache